[6] Philippines (Valenzuela)
Date: Fri, 26 Aug 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Manila Times, Philippines, 26 Aug 2005 [edited]
<http://www.manilatimes.net/national/2005/aug/26/yehey/metro/20050826met1.html>

The Valenzuela City government has declared a dengue outbreak in the 2nd
district, since 78 percent of 222 people afflicted with the deadly disease in
the city came from the area.
Dr. Manuel Mapue, the city epidemiologist, said 3 victims have already
died. "But this week, we received only 4 additional cases, unlike the previous
weeks," Mapue said.
There are 9 barangays in the 2nd District but only 5 -- Marulas, General T. de
Leon, Karuhatan, Maysan and Ugong -- are being monitored for dengue cases.
Most of the dengue patients in the city were confined at the Valenzuela City
General Hospital, San Lazaro Hospital, Fatima Medical Center and Calalang
General Hospital.
Mapue said the declaration of a dengue outbreak on Monday in the district has
helped in persuading the residents to clean their surroundings and eliminate
breeding grounds of mosquitoes.
"There are initiatives among [the residents] but . . . the city government
helps them. We continue our fumigation activities and spraying [Abate] powder
to kill larvae and eggs," he added.
Last year [2004], Valenzuela had 551 cases of dengue. 3 of the victims died.
[Byline: Ronnie E. Calumpita]
